Commands.Body:
<center>The Shape tile modifier allows you to assign shapes to your
tiles.  Nearby are some examples of the Shape tool at work.  There are
16 shapes currently available - four cardinal ramp shapes, four interior
corners, four exterior corners and four diagonal cutoff shapes.</center>

Commands.Body:
<center>Note the water tiles surrounding this courtyard - those are the
only tiles on this map that have assigned Passability to them.  Generally
in 3D mode you'll want to allow the terrain and physics calculations to do
the actual passability, but exceptions can be made</center>

<center>Please, study these maps and how things are constructed both
in the 2D editor view and how that reflects in the 3D space... and if you
have any questions please ask in our Discord server!</center>

CharacterModel.Name: Tiles\Final Boss Blues - Time Fantasy Limited\RPGA OpenRTP-32\RPGA-RTP-FlatAndDoodad.png

Commands.Body:
<center>The trees and fences shown on this map are doodads.  Importantly,
doodads will place on a layer's Base Height.  This is important when using
Structure tiles as - unless you assign a height to the Structure tile - Entities,
Player sprites and Doodads will appear underneath the ground as seen on
the platform above.
Always remember to assign height values to your Structure tiles!</center>

<center>Doodad Customization
Within the map editor window, when in Doodad Mode, you can individually
override each individual doodad's default scalar and rotational values by
right-clicking on the doodad you would like to customize and editing the
values that apply to just that doodad.  Otherwise, the doodad will appear
just as defined in the Database.</center>

Commands.Body:
<center>Welcome to the RPGA 3D Mapping Sample!

This is a simple look at 3D map layout and showcases layering Structure,
Animated and Standard terraforming and flat tiles, as well as showing
examples of some shapes possible with the Shape tile modifier. </center>

<center>Doodads will also be shown and are a versatile tool in your
3D toolbox... as tempting as it may be to use terraforming autotiles
and animated tiles for everything, doodads will be an invaluable part
of crafting your environments in the future of RPGA.
</center>
